  "source_notes": "Richard Ideman quotes Cosmic Seed magazine.  Robert Jansky gives 1:45 PM from Astrological Review, 1973/74.  Penfield Collection quotes both sources for 1:59 PM.  Different reports give his birth place as Cajamarca, Peru or Sao Paulo, Brazil.\\n[wiki-code]In July 2014, Lepoivre mentions  Kannon McAfee as a source for 9 am birthtime. On 12 July 2014 McAffee wrote on the forum:\"I possess a photocopy of the original birth certificate from Cajamarca, Peru. For years times around 2 pm have been passed around after the 5 March 1973 TIME magazine cover article. It appears that a TIME magazine Peruvian correspondent glanced at the birth manifest record made the next day at 2:30 PM and mistook this for the birth time. In fact the document clearly shows that the date of birth was on 25 December 1925 at \"nueve a.m.\" Nine AM.  \". A day later he posted a copy of the BC on the forum.\\n",
